<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <% include partials/header %>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400;600&family=Karla:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #c9963a;
      --gold-light: #e8bc68;
      --deep: #1a0f00;
      --cream: #fdf6ec;
      --muted: #8a7560;
      --text: #3a2810;
    }

    .styled-page {
      background: var(--cream);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: 'Karla', sans-serif;
      padding-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 24px 36px;
      position: relative;
    }

    .page-header::after {
      content: '';
      display: block;
      width: 60px;
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--gold);
      margin: 24px auto 0;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--deep);
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .page-header .subtitle {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-top: 8px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .section-nav {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px 24px 10px;
    }

    .section-nav a {
      color: var(--gold);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      transition: color 0.3s;
      padding: 4px 0;
    }

    .section-nav a:hover { color: var(--deep); }

    .section-nav .sep {
      color: var(--gold-light);
      margin: 0 10px;
    }

    .page-intro {
      font-size: 1.12rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px 10px;
      line-height: 1.85;
    }

    .page-content {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px;
    }

    .page-section {
      padding: 32px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201, 150, 58, 0.15);
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
      scroll-margin-top: 80px;
    }

    .page-section.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    .page-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .page-section h2 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }

    .page-section:hover h2 { color: var(--deep); }

    .page-section p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--text);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .page-section ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .page-section ul li {
      padding: 8px 0;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .page-section ul li::before {
      content: '\2022';
      color: var(--gold);
      font-weight: bold;
      display: inline-block;
      width: 1em;
    }

    .page-section a {
      color: var(--gold);
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold-light);
      transition: color 0.3s, border-color 0.3s;
    }

    .page-section a:hover {
      color: var(--deep);
      border-color: var(--deep);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <% include partials/menu %>
    <div class="container bg-light">
      <div class="styled-page">
        <div class="page-header">
          <p class="subtitle">Youth Programs</p>
          <h1>Ghanshyam Bal Mandal</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="section-nav">
          <a href="#dharmik">Dharmik</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#gujarati">Gujarati</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#music">Music</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#team">Team</a><span class="sep">&middot;</span>
          <a href="#additional-activities">Additional Activities</a>
        </div>

        <p class="page-intro">When Ghanshyam Maharaj took residence in Sydney in 2013, we committed to fully utilising
          our Mandir&rsquo;s facilities to serve the new generation of children. Today, we offer a wide range of activities,
          including Ghanshyam Dharmik, Ghanshyam Gujarati, and Ghanshyam Music classes. As of 2024, with 210 students
          enrolled, GBM continues to provide diverse and enriching programs that nurture the spiritual, cultural, and
          personal growth of our young haribhakto.</p>

        <div class="page-content">

          <div id="dharmik" class="page-section">
            <h2>Ghanshyam Dharmik</h2>
            <p>In 2014, we launched Ghanshyam Dharmik classes using materials from Bhuj Mandir. As the number of
              first-generation Australian children grew, we recognised the need for a more tailored approach. As part
              of the GBM refresh in 2018, we developed interactive, colourful workbooks and teacher support materials
              specifically for our local students.</p>
            <p>Building on the success of our local content, we contributed to the making of an international
              syllabus. With the blessings of Bhagwan Shree Swaminarayan, Bhuj Mahant Swami, and esteemed Vadil Santo,
              we introduced the Svadhyay syllabus in 2022, developed with contributions from the UK and Australia.
              This world-class framework, designed for youth aged 6 to 16, promotes self-improvement, Vedic study, and
              self-reflection, alongside core interpersonal and life skills. The Svadhyay syllabus empowers children
              to understand and appreciate satsang, ensuring the strength and continuity of our religion for future
              generations.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="gujarati" class="page-section">
            <h2>Ghanshyam Gujarati</h2>
            <p>Established in 2003, Ghanshyam Gujarati has been dedicated to nurturing young minds and instilling the
              rich cultural heritage of Gujarat into the hearts of future generations. Our mission is to create a
              supportive environment where children can learn, grow, and connect with their Gujarati roots. Through
              interactive lessons, cultural activities, and language instruction, we aim to foster pride in our
              students&rsquo; cultural identity and enhance their language skills, enabling them to preserve their mother
              tongue and read sacred shastras.</p>
            <p>Our curriculum, originally based on textbooks created in 1997 by Willesden Mandir in the UK, has been
              thoughtfully updated to meet modern teaching standards. It incorporates engaging activities that keep
              our students actively involved in their learning journey.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="music" class="page-section">
            <h2>Ghanshyam Music</h2>
            <p>In 2019, we expanded our offerings to include music classes, featuring tabla, keyboard, and singing
              classes. These classes are designed to nurture and develop musical talent, instilling a deep appreciation
              for Indian classical music among our youth. Ghanshyam Music provides a comprehensive cultural education
              that enriches the spiritual and cultural lives of our young haribhakto. Our music program not only fosters
              artistic growth but also strengthens their connection to the rich musical heritage of our Sampraday.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="team" class="page-section">
            <h2>Teaching Team</h2>
            <p>We are always seeking dedicated individuals to join our teaching team. If you have a passion for
              education and a desire to teach Dharmik, Gujarati or Music, consider becoming a teacher with us! To
              express your interest, please fill out our
              <a href="https://tinyurl.com/GBM-Teach" target="_blank">Teacher Application Form</a>,
              and we will reach out to discuss this wonderful opportunity further.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="additional-activities" class="page-section">
            <h2>Additional Activities of GBM Sydney</h2>
            <p>In addition to our classes, we conduct many other activities for our youngest haribhakto.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Public Speaking Training:</strong> We provide training to help our youth develop their public
                speaking skills, boosting their confidence and communication abilities.</li>
              <li><strong>Youth Parayan in English:</strong> These sessions allow our youth to explore and listen to
                religious texts in English, making them more accessible and engaging.</li>
              <li><strong>Annual Cultural Show:</strong> This vibrant event showcases the talents of our youth in dance,
                singing, instrumental music, drama, and pyramids, celebrating our rich cultural heritage.</li>
              <li><strong>Camps:</strong> We organise immersive camps every year that combine fun activities with life
                skills and spiritual education.</li>
              <li><strong>School Holiday Outings:</strong> These outings offer fun and educational experiences, helping
                children bond and learn in a relaxed environment.</li>
              <li><strong>Weekly Sports:</strong> Regular sports activities ensure that our youth stay active and
                healthy, fostering teamwork and discipline.</li>
              <li><strong>Teacher Training Sessions:</strong> Our teaching team participates in training sessions to
                stay abreast of the latest educational methods and to enhance their teaching skills.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <script>
    var observer = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
      entries.forEach(function (e) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); observer.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.15 });
    document.querySelectorAll('.page-section').forEach(function (el) { observer.observe(el); });
  </script>

  <% include partials/footer %>
</body>

</html>
